                    <msContents class="lemmatic">
                        
                        <summary>
                            This is <persName ref="viaf.org/viaf/19690624">Ḥunayn ibn Ishaq</persName>'s Translation of Galen's commentary on the Hippocratic Aphorisms. The beginning of each Book is as follows:
                            Bk1: 1a; Bk2: 23b; Bk3: 45a; Bk4: 62a (missing the first several folios; so it begins in the middle of comm. on lemma iv. 13); Bk5: 79b; Bk6: 102a; Bk7: 128b.
                        </summary>  
                           
